<type>[optional scope]: <description>

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Example:
# feat(lang): add russian language
#
# (Max 50 char)
#
# Type can be:
#
# ᛫ feat     - a new feature
# ᛫ fix      - a bug fix
# ᛫ refactor - a code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# ᛫ chore    - dependencies or similar
# ᛫ docs     - documentation only changes
# ᛫ style    - changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# ᛫ perf     - a code change that improves performance
# ᛫ hack     - a temporary fix to make things move forward
# ᛫ wip      - for intermediate commits to keep patches reasonably sized
# ᛫ BREAKING CHANGE - something that breaks other changes
#
